// 2026-06-02 audit (Agent 4 A1): container monomorphization with a
// non-simple type argument (`?T`, `*T`, `[]T`) emits an invalid C
// identifier `Box_?u32` containing `?`. GCC then errors with a
// confusing message far from the ZER source.
//
// Fix candidates:
//   (a) checker rejects non-identifier type args with a clear ZER error
//   (b) emitter mangles ? → opt_, * → ptr_, [] → slice_
//
// Currently the failure escapes from the ZER frontend into GCC's lexer.

container Box(T) {
    T value;
    u32 tag;
}

void main() {
    Box(?u32) b;
}
